To simplify \(-\tfrac{54}{42}\), factor out a \(6\) from numerator and denominator:

\[
-\frac{54}{42}
= -\frac{6\cdot 9}{6\cdot 7}
= -\frac{9}{7}.
\]

To simplify \(-\tfrac{81}{45}\), divide numerator and denominator by their GCD, which is 9:

\[
-\frac{81}{45}
= -\frac{81\div 9}{45\div 9}
= -\frac{9}{5}.
\]

To multiply, first note that a negative times a negative is positive. Then multiply numerators and denominators and simplify:

\[
-\frac{4}{7}\;\times\;-\frac{5}{8}
=\;+\frac{4\cdot 5}{7\cdot 8}
=\;\frac{20}{56}
=\;\frac{20\div 4}{56\div 4}
=\;\frac{5}{14}.
\]

To multiply, first note the negative sign will carry through. Then multiply numerators and denominators:

\[
-\,\frac{9}{20}\times\frac{5}{12}
=-\frac{9\cdot5}{20\cdot12}
=-\frac{45}{240}.
\]

Now simplify \(\tfrac{45}{240}\) by dividing top and bottom by 15:

\[
-\frac{45}{240}
=-\frac{45\div15}{240\div15}
=-\frac{3}{16}.
\]

Answer: \(\displaystyle -\frac{3}{16}\).

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{3}{5}\div\frac{p}{7}
=\frac{3}{5}\times\frac{7}{p}
=\frac{3\cdot 7}{5\cdot p}
=\frac{21}{5p}.
\]

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
\frac{5}{8}\div\frac{q}{3}
=\frac{5}{8}\times\frac{3}{q}
=\frac{5\cdot3}{8\cdot q}
=\frac{15}{8q},
\]

where \(q\neq0\).

To divide, multiply by the reciprocal:

\[
-\frac{2}{3}\div\Bigl(-\frac{5}{6}\Bigr)
= -\frac{2}{3}\times\frac{6}{-5}
=\frac{(-2)\cdot6}{3\cdot(-5)}
=\frac{-12}{-15}
=\frac{12}{15}
=\frac{4}{5}.
\]

Answer: \(\displaystyle \frac{4}{5}\).

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
-\frac{5}{6}\;\div\;\bigl(-\tfrac{2}{3}\bigr)
=\;-\frac{5}{6}\times\bigl(-\tfrac{3}{2}\bigr)
=\frac{(-5)\cdot3}{6\cdot(-2)}
=\frac{-15}{-12}
=\frac{15}{12}
=\frac{5}{4}.
\]
